<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="29" pageNumber="28">
Distribution: Krishna, Godavary, Ganges, Brahmaputra, Irrawaddy, Salween, Chao Phraya, Mekong and drainages throughout the Malay Peninsula and Indonesia (Roberts, 
<pageStartToken pageNumber="29">1983</pageStartToken>
(in part); Kottelat, 1989; Talwar &amp; Jingran, 1991; Rainboth, 1996; Jayaram, 1999 (in part); Karmakar, 2000; Kottelat, 2001a). It has also been reported from the Indus drainage (Talwar &amp; Jingran, 1991; Jayaram, 1999; Karmakar, 2000) and Cauvery drainage in southern India (as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F741BB56-1879-480A-8E9E-3C7A69B88F8A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pimelodidae" genus="Pimelodus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pimelodus carnaticus Jerdon 1849:341" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carnaticus">Pimelodus carnaticus</taxonomicName>
) by Jerdon (1849). It was reported as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:449542DD-FEE6-44E8-AFB4-6DC639C50D32" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Bagarius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pimelodus bagarius Hamilton 1822:186, 378" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bagarius">B. bagarius</taxonomicName>
in the Godavary drainage by David (1963). This species is replaced by 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C2689E57-91C7-49B5-8003-3A91CFF83E8D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Bagarius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bagarius rutilus Ng &amp; Kottelat 2000:10" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rutilus">B. rutilus</taxonomicName>
in the Red River drainage in Vietnam and China (Ng &amp; Kottelat, 2000; Kottelat, 2001a; Kottelat, 2001b).
</paragraph>
